<li id="cite_note-57"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-57">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Mercer_Cook" title="Mercer Cook">Mercer Cook</a>, African-American scholar of French culture wrote: "His (Langston Hughes) work had a lot to do with the famous concept of <i>Négritude</i>, of black soul and feeling, that they were beginning to develop." Rampersad, vol. 1, 1986, p. 343.</span>
