<li id="cite_note-59"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Charlotte Mason generously supported Hughes for two years. She supervised his writing his first novel, <i>Not Without Laughter</i> (1930). Her patronage of Hughes ended about the time the novel appeared. Rampersad. "Langston Hughes", in <i>The Concise Oxford Companion to African American Literature</i>, 2001, p. 207.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Tanenhaus_1997-60"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Tanenhaus_1997_60-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Tanenhaus_1997_60-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r999302996"/><cite id="CITEREFTanenhaus1997" class="citation book cs1">Tanenhaus, Sam (1997). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=vzkFpiXCF8wC&amp;lpg=PP1"><i>Whittaker Chambers: A Biography</i></a>. Random House. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780307789266" title="Special:BookSources/9780307789266"><bdi>9780307789266</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Whittaker+Chambers%3A+A+Biography&amp;rft.pub=Random+House&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.isbn=9780307789266&amp;rft.aulast=Tanenhaus&amp;rft.aufirst=Sam&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DvzkFpiXCF8wC%26lpg%3DPP1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALangston+Hughes" class="Z3988"></span></span>
